Pancreatico-colonic fistula after acute necrotizing pancreatitis. Diagnosis with spiral CT using rectal water soluble contrast media. Colonic complications are rare but lethal events in acute pancreatitis.We report the case of a 42-year-old man who suffered from a pancreatico-colonic fistula following a necrosectomy for severe pancreatitis the fistula was demonstrated by spiral computed tomography using rectal water soluble contrast media.Computed tomography with rectal contrast detects pancreatico-colonic fistulas.